cs.ET, cs.IT, cs.OH, cs.LG, cs.AI 

The paper discusses a method for programming photonic mesh networks for applications such as machine learning and quantum information processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.OH (Optimization and Control), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.ET and cs.IT are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a new approach for programming photonic networks that is fault-tolerant and can reduce programming time. However, the paper also includes a demonstration of the approach on a feedforward optical neural network model trained to classify handwritten digit images, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.LG and cs.AI categories. Finally, the paper's emphasis on photonic networks suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.OH category, which focuses on optimization and control of optical systems.
